advisory_title: CVE-2023-26031 Privilege escalation in Apache Haoop Yarn container-executor binary on Linux systems
recommendations: Revert the change made in YARN-10495, which is done in hadoop-3.3.5. Verify the vulnerability using the readelf command. Ensure that the container-executor binary is not vulnerable to privilege escalation.

advisory_title: CVE-2021-25642 Apache Hadoop YARN remote code execution in ZKConfigurationStore of capacity scheduler
recommendations: Upgrade to fixed versions 2.10.2, 3.2.4, 3.3.4. Ensure proper validation of data obtained from ZooKeeper to prevent remote code execution.

advisory_title: CVE-2022-25168 Command injection in org.apache.hadoop.fs.FileUtil.unTarUsingTar
recommendations: Upgrade to fixed versions 2.10.2, 3.2.4, 3.3.3. Ensure proper input validation to prevent command injection attacks.

advisory_title: CVE-2021-33036 Apache Hadoop Privilege escalation vulnerability
recommendations: Upgrade to fixed versions 2.10.2, 3.2.3, 3.3.2. Remove permission to escalate to yarn user from users who can escalate but cannot escalate to root user.

advisory_title: CVE-2021-37404 Heap buffer overflow in libhdfs native library
recommendations: Upgrade to fixed versions 2.10.2, 3.2.3, 3.3.2. Validate user input to prevent heap buffer overflow attacks.

advisory_title: CVE-2022-26612 Arbitrary file write during untar on Windows
recommendations: Avoid running YARN daemons as users with symlink creation permissions on Windows. Avoid using symlinks in tar files to prevent arbitrary file writes.

advisory_title: Issue With IAM Supporting Multiple MFA Devices
recommendations: As of April 21, 2023, the identified issue has been remediated by requiring that IAM users who already have one or more MFAs and who use AK/SK credentials to manage their own MFA devices to first use sts:GetSessionToken and an existing MFA to obtain MFA-enabled temporary credentials to sign their CLI commands or API requests prior to enabling or disabling MFA devices for themselves. We have directly notified a very small number of customers via their Personal Health Dashboard who had previously associated an additional MFA device using a mechanism other than the AWS Management Console. We recommended that those notified customers confirm the correctness of their MFA configurations. No further customer action is required.

advisory_title: Risky command safeguards bypass in Dashboard Examples Hub
recommendations: For Splunk Enterprise, upgrade versions to 9.2.1, 9.1.4, 9.0.9, or higher. For Splunk Cloud Platform, Splunk has put in place a mitigation, and is actively monitoring and rolling out patches across Splunk Cloud Platform instances. On Splunk Enterprise, you can mitigate the vulnerability by removing the template file for the Splunk Dashboard Studio Examples Hub. This file is located at $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/splunk-dashboard-studio/appserver/templates/example-hub.html. This mitigation prevents the Dashboard Examples Hub from rendering. The vulnerability affects instances with Splunk Web turned on. You can turn Splunk Web off as a possible workaround. The Splunk-built Splunk Dashboard Studio app comes with Splunk Enterprise and uses the Dashboard Examples Hub. You can disable the app as a possible workaround for instances that do not run as Search Heads.
mitigation_techniques: ['Upgrade software versions', 'Remove template file', 'Turn off Splunk Web']

advisory_title: Splunk Authentication Token Exposure in Debug Log in Splunk Enterprise
recommendations: To determine the current global logging mode on the instance, visit the Server Logging Settings page in Splunk Web. If debug logging is on, either globally or for the JsonWebToken component, remedy the problem by upgrading Splunk Enterprise to versions 9.2.1, 9.1.4, 9.0.9, or higher. Delete the log files and events related to the JsonWebToken component. Rotate any potentially exposed authentication tokens. If it isn't currently possible to upgrade to a fixed version of Splunk Enterprise, turn off debug logging, turn off token authentication if not in use, and raise the JsonWebToken component logging level to INFO.
mitigation_techniques: ['Upgrade software versions', 'Delete log files', 'Delete events', 'Rotate authentication tokens']
